item.title: Data Wrangling and Visualization with Snowshoe Hares/Principal Components Analysis (PCA)
item.description: Data wrangling and visualization with snowshoe hares (Lepus americanus) This section of the project concerns data wrangling and data visualization with populations of snowshoe hares (Lepus americanus) in Bonanza Creek, Alaska. The study concerns 5 locales in Tanana Valley in central Alaska from study sites Tok in the east to Clear in the west from 1999-2012 with a time horizon of 13 years.
